name: Billy Bean
summary: Billy Bean, a pioneering baseball figure and advocate for LGBTQ inclusion, passed away at 60. Bean, who played in the MLB and later became an executive with the league, was the second openly gay former MLB player. Throughout his career, Bean dedicated himself to promoting diversity and inclusion in baseball, working with the MLB's Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion department. He was instrumental in creating the league's first LGBTQ employee resource group and advocated for policies to make baseball more welcoming for LGBTQ players and fans. Bean's work had a profound impact on the sport, making baseball a more inclusive environment for all.

summary: Daisy Ridley, the actress known for her role in the "Star Wars" franchise, has disclosed her diagnosis of Graves' disease. name: Trinity Rodman
summary: Trinity Rodman emerged as a rising star in the world of women's soccer after scoring a crucial goal in the quarterfinals of the Tokyo Olympics. The daughter of former NBA legend Dennis Rodman, she propelled the USWNT to a 1-0 victory over Japan in extra time. Despite her game-winning strike, Rodman claims to have "blacked out" during the moment, highlighting the intensity of the match. The media has praised Rodman's performance, citing her goal as "the best moment of her career" and a "brilliant curler" that gave the USWNT the lead. She is recognized for her exceptional skills and contributions to the team's Olympic success.

summary: Kevin Durant has been a key contributor for Team USA at the 2024 Olympics, despite coming off the bench in the knockout stage. In the game against South Sudan, his performance set the internet ablaze. Durant surpassed Lisa Leslie as the all-time leading scorer for Team USA in the Olympics, and also overtook Brazil in the semi-finals. His teammates, including Anthony Edwards, have praised his impact on the team. However, head coach Steve Kerr has stated that there are no plans for Durant to start as he continues to recover from an injury.
